                            <comment id="13474029" author="smitaw" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 11:54:29 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch contains the write stuff for cUsigma , if enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474032" author="smitaw" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 11:55:41 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;PFA the patch for writing USigma file for ssvd &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474246" author="dlyubimov" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 16:46:45 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I dont think either issue or patch is valid. Ssvd writes multiple outputs, and doesnt cram  all the files to same output directory.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474288" author="smitaw" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 17:27:30 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I could see U, V and sigma(diagonal matrix) written in the output directory, whereas all the stuff is written in temp directory . May be I am missing something, but when I set param  uSigma to true , then it was not written in output directory , where as if I set computeU and computeV to true -&amp;gt; it writes in output directory as out/U/ and  out/V/ and out/sigma but not out/Usigma . May be I am missing something.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474343" author="dlyubimov" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 18:27:38 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Are you sure? Are you using latest trunk?&lt;br/&gt;
Still don&apos;t see the problem. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;This is the way U paths are set up : &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;

      Path svPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Sigma&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path uPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;U&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path uSigmaPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;USigma&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path uHalfSigmaPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;UHalfSigma&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path vPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;V&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path vHalfSigmaPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;VHalfSigma&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);
      Path vSigmaPath = &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; Path(outputPath, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;VSigma&quot;&lt;/span&gt;);


&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;And one person who was using U*Sigma output actually confirmed it worked fine for him... all outputs are saved in output folder but form hierarchy&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;so basically outputs should be as &lt;br/&gt;
output/Sigma &amp;#8211; singular values &lt;br/&gt;
output/U &amp;#8211; U&lt;br/&gt;
output/V &amp;#8211; V&lt;br/&gt;
output/USigma &amp;#8211; U*Sigma &lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and so on per above. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Keep in mind that U and V are enabled by default and USigma is disabled. I guess you need to use something like &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mahout ssvd -k 80 --pca -U false -V false --us true &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;to get the desired outcome.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474411" author="dlyubimov" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 19:33:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;i could reproduce. It&apos;s not clear to me yet why it lands where it lands though so far.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474451" author="dlyubimov" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 20:33:05 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, &lt;br/&gt;
there are more issues with moving the result to output folder. &lt;br/&gt;
on top of it -ow flag was not working as it should. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try now from the turnk, it is working for me. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the command line i used was &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;

bin/mahout ssvd -i /DRM-sparse -o /SSVD-out -ow -k 80  -V &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; -U &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;false&lt;/span&gt; -us &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; -t 2

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13474452" author="dlyubimov" created="Thu, 11 Oct 2012 20:34:03 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;committed to trunk, removing and fixing some unnecessarily slow dipping mechanisms in the command line houskeeping&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
